<body>
  <h1>Yammie Foodies</h1>
  <h2>Easy & Tasty Chapati by Kemmy KE Cooks</h2>

  <div class="ingredients">
    <h3>Ingredients (for 10 Chapatis)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>4 cups all-purpose flour</li>
      <li>1/2 of a small pumpkin</li>
      <li>1/2 tablespoon salt</li>
      <li>1/2 tablespoon sugar</li>
      <li>1/4 cup water</li>
      <li>Vegetable oil</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="instructions">
    <h3>Cooking Instructions</h3>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 1:</strong> Cook and mash the pumpkin.
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 2:</strong> Prepare the dough: in a bowl mix the pumpkin, the flour, the salt, the sugar and some oil; using water, make an elastic and well-moist paste.
      <br><em>[Insert picture of step 2]</em>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 3:</strong> Cover and leave the dough to rest for 10 min.
      <br><em>[Insert picture of step 3]</em>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 4:</strong> Roll flat the dough and make a big circle, then brush with oil.
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 5:</strong> Cut long pieces of the dough.
      <br><em>[Insert picture of step 5]</em>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 6:</strong> Fold and roll with both hands from the ends to make a rope-like shape and make coiled balls.
      <br><em>[Insert picture of step 6]</em>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 7:</strong> Roll the coiled balls flat and make smaller circular shapes (1 ball = 1 chapati).
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 8:</strong> Heat a frying pan and fry the chapati on both sides (they need to be cooked without browning).
      <br><em>[Insert picture of step 8]</em>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 9:</strong> Fry the chapatis again while brushing them with oil to keep them moist...they are ready when both sides are golden brown.
      <br><em>[Insert picture of step 9]</em>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 10:</strong> Use some foil to keep the chapatis warm while you are frying (you will need to keep them warm to be able to shape them properly before serving).
      <br><em>[Insert picture of step 10]</em>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 11:</strong> You can serve the chapatis by folding them in a triangle shape.
      <br><em>[Insert picture of step 11]</em>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
